                    "get_section_description_filter": "To create objects that are refined, infused with meaning, you will develop the skills to transform your materials from the basic forms into the nuanced shapes that set your work apart from others..Through a series of explorations of surface embellishment, mechanisms, stone setting, and metalsmithing techniques \u2013 both new and old \u2013 you will greatly advance your ability to transform your ideas into powerful objects that have conceptual rigor and intention of form. Design, ideation, problem-solving and research will all complement the practical skills you will learn as you delve deeper into the possibilities of creating great artwork that holds space in the world.&nbsp;2A and 2B can be taken in either order.They are a requirements for JMA Majors. Any major college wide can take these courses as an elective with the prerequisite of METAL 1000.",
