                    "get_section_description_filter": "<span>Lithography is the wonderful printmaking technique where artists can draw or paint directly onto the surface of stone or aluminum plate. Next, artists chemically etch and fix it onto the matrix to create prints with a wide range of drawn/painted marks. We describe it as a kind of alchemical magic, that captures incredible detail, tone and colour in Printmedia. This course covers demonstrations and hands-on work in the both physical and digital techniques of lithographic printing on stone, ball-grained plate, and photo-plate. Many drawing/painting techniques and materials will be explored and careful attention will be given to the process of etching, proofing, correcting, and printing editions. Students are encouraged to explore creative methods that meet individual aesthetic and conceptual needs. </span><span>Open to advanced students from any major.</span>",
